snippet.textDisplay:
this comment section is just...


it's 90% "nola got robbed she did everything and was perf", 5% "nola deserved it" and 5% "it was so obvious lmao bryce isnt a gamer i knew from the start"


it's annoying to see this on a video but i don't know what i expected from a channel with "Guess my ethnicity" and "Do all comedians think the same"


The males were not sexist--- atleast, it wasn't at play on any round except for maybe the first at most.


They had their reasons to be suspicious at both.


Bryce gave the simplest, most basic answer about a game from YEARS ago, after saying he played 90's horror games--- He could've been a retro gamer who's not very steeped in modern titles. That's still technically a gamer. Jessica gave an answer that was more complex, and used some terminology some players don't use--- Like calling towers turrets. Not all the players who play use it--- It's very likely none of the others heard that terminology before. "Farming, uh... Turrets" is also not a very compelling argument in her favor. I can't talk on much else, as I don't personally play league. I never found it enjoyable.


Bryce could've gotten the name wrong. Bryce would've been voted out that round. However...
It felt like Nora was delaying that entire round by arguing with Bryce for so long--- AND SHE ALSO got the name wrong.
They also bonded while she was arguing. They wouldn't have bonded as much if they had been allowed to participate.

Similarly, There's only 4 sonic games on GBA. Sonic adventure 1/2 aren't among them. Three sonic advance games, and then also, the fighter--- I don't remember its name, and don't wanna bother looking it up right now.


She wanted to prove herself above Bryce, despite ALSO being wrong. So they voted her out after Bryce, because they DIDN'T TRUST HER.
In the final round, they trusted her the least, and absolutely had to vote someone out. So she got voted out. Don't fault them for that final round. She also kept her hand down.


There MIGHT'VE been some sexism at play. If so, that sucks. It's too late to do anything about it. The money's already been given out. I understand, sexism sucks. But not everything where females get voted out is sexism. If you cry sexism at everything, then no-one will take you seriously when you DO cry sexism, and mean it. It's just like the boy who cried wolf.


I'm hoping alot from you guys to listen to this, considering how rabid the comments seem, and I don't expect good results--- but it's good to hold a little hope every now and then, isn't it? No matter how hard it is to do nowadays.


Also yes, all of them were very annoying to listen to. The females were the least annoying. The males were funny haha "let's t-pose" characters.
I'm simply saying not everything is sexism, although they could've very well been doing a "haha funny sexism." It doesn't matter now, does it? The money's already given out. Posting a youtube comment on "HOW NOLA GOT ROBBED" isn't gonna re-do the timeline.
